ork), so that we can insert the
             route in the kernel table without it being complained about. A=
 boolean, defaults to "<code class=3D"literal">no</code>".
             </p></dd><dt id=3D"Destination=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code =
class=3D"varname">Destination=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=
=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/sy=
stemd/man/systemd.network.html#Destination=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The de=
stination prefix of the route. Possibly
            followed by a slash and the prefix length. If omitted, a
            full-length host route is assumed.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Source=3D"=
><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">Source=3D</code></span><a cla=
ss=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.free=
desktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#Source=3D">=C2=B6</a>=
</dt><dd><p>The source prefix of the route. Possibly followed by
            a slash and the prefix length. If omitted, a full-length
            host route is assumed.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Metric=3D"><span class=
=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">Metric=3D</code></span><a class=3D"header=
link" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/=
software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#Metric=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>=
The metric of the route (an unsigned integer).</p></dd><dt id=3D"IPv6Prefer=
ence=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">IPv6Preference=3D</co=
de></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"=
https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#IPv6P=
reference=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Specifies the route preference as defin=
ed in <a class=3D"ulink" href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4191" targe=
t=3D"_top">RFC4191</a> for Router Discovery messages.
            Which can be one of "<code class=3D"literal">low</code>" the ro=
ute has a lowest priority,
            "<code class=3D"literal">medium</code>" the route has a default=
 priority or
            "<code class=3D"literal">high</code>" the route has a highest p=
riority.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Scope=3D1"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"v=
arname">Scope=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to=
 this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/system=
d.network.html#Scope=3D1">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The scope of the route, whi=
ch can be "<code class=3D"literal">global</code>",
            "<code class=3D"literal">link</code>" or "<code class=3D"litera=
l">host</code>". Defaults to
            "<code class=3D"literal">global</code>".</p></dd><dt id=3D"Pref=
erredSource=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">PreferredSourc=
e=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" =
href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.ht=
ml#PreferredSource=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The preferred source address o=
f the route. The address
            must be in the format described in
            <a href=3D"http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man3/inet_pton.3.htm=
l"><span class=3D"citerefentry"><span class=3D"refentrytitle">inet_pton</sp=
an>(3)</span></a>.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Table=3Dnum"><span class=3D"term"><cod=
e class=3D"varname">Table=3D<em class=3D"replaceable"><code>num</code></em>=
</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=
=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#T=
able=3Dnum">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The table identifier for the route (a num=
ber between 1 and 4294967295, or 0 to unset).
          The table can be retrieved using <span class=3D"command"><strong>=
ip route show table <em class=3D"replaceable"><code>num</code></em></strong=
></span>.
          </p></dd><dt id=3D"Protocol=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=
=3D"varname">Protocol=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Perm=
alink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/ma=
n/systemd.network.html#Protocol=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The Protocol iden=
tifier for the route. Takes a number between 0 and 255 or the special value=
s
            "<code class=3D"literal">kernel</code>", "<code class=3D"litera=
l">boot</code>" and "<code class=3D"literal">static</code>". Defaults to
            "<code class=3D"literal">static</code>".
            </p></dd><dt id=3D"Type=3D1"><span class=3D"term"><code class=
=3D"varname">Type=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalin=
k to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/sy=
stemd.network.html#Type=3D1">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The Type identifier for =
special route types, which can be
            "<code class=3D"literal">unicast</code>" route to a destination=
 network address which describes the path to the destination,
            "<code class=3D"literal">blackhole</code>" packets are discarde=
d silently,
            "<code class=3D"literal">unreachable</code>" packets are discar=
ded and the ICMP message host unreachable is generated,
            "<code class=3D"literal">prohibit</code>" packets are discarded=
 and the ICMP message communication administratively
            prohibited is generated. Defaults to "<code class=3D"literal">u=
nicast</code>".
            </p></dd><dt id=3D"InitialCongestionWindow=3D"><span class=3D"t=
erm"><code class=3D"varname">InitialCongestionWindow=3D</code></span><a cla=
ss=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.free=
desktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#InitialCongestionWind=
ow=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The TCP initial congestion window is used duri=
ng the start of a TCP connection. During the start of a TCP
            session, when a client requests a resource, the server's initia=
l congestion window determines how many data bytes
            will be sent during the initial burst of data. Takes a size in =
bytes between 1 and 4294967295 (2^32 - 1). The usual
            suffixes K, M, G are supported and are understood to the base o=
f 1024. Defaults to unset.
            </p></dd><dt id=3D"InitialAdvertisedReceiveWindow=3D"><span cla=
ss=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">InitialAdvertisedReceiveWindow=3D</code=
></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"ht=
tps://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#Initial=
AdvertisedReceiveWindow=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The TCP initial advertise=
d receive window is the amount of receive data (in bytes) that can initally=
 be buffered at one time
            on a connection. The sending host can send only that amount of =
data before waiting for an acknowledgment and window update
            from the receiving host. Takes a size in bytes between 1 and 42=
94967295 (2^32 - 1). The usual suffixes K, M, G are supported
            and are understood to the base of 1024. Defaults to unset.
            </p></dd><dt id=3D"QuickAck=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code clas=
s=3D"varname">QuickAck=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Per=
malink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/m=
an/systemd.network.html#QuickAck=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Takes a boolean =
argument. When true enables TCP quick ack mode for the route. Defaults to u=
nset.
            </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class=3D"refsect1"><a name=3D"id=
-1.13"></a><h2 id=3D"[DHCP] Section Options">[DHCP] Section Options<a class=
=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this headline" href=3D"https://www.fr=
eedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#%5BDHCP%5D%20Sectio=
n%20Options">=C2=B6</a></h2><p>The "<code class=3D"literal">[DHCP]</code>" =
section configures the
      DHCPv4 and DHCP6 client, if it is enabled with the
      <code class=3D"varname">DHCP=3D</code> setting described above:</p><d=
iv class=3D"variablelist"><dl class=3D"variablelist"><dt id=3D"UseDNS=3D"><=
span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">UseDNS=3D</code></span><a class=
=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freede=
sktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#UseDNS=3D">=C2=B6</a></=
dt><dd><p>When true (the default), the DNS servers received
            from the DHCP server will be used and take precedence over
            any statically configured ones.</p><p>This corresponds to the <=
code class=3D"option">nameserver</code>
            option in <a href=3D"http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man5/resol=
v.conf.5.html"><span class=3D"citerefentry"><span class=3D"refentrytitle">r=
esolv.conf</span>(5)</span></a>.</p></dd><dt id=3D"UseNTP=3D"><span class=
=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">UseNTP=3D</code></span><a class=3D"header=
link" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/=
software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#UseNTP=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>=
When true (the default), the NTP servers received
            from the DHCP server will be used by systemd-timesyncd
            and take precedence over any statically configured ones.</p></d=
d><dt id=3D"UseMTU=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">UseMTU=
=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" h=
ref=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.htm=
l#UseMTU=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>When true, the interface maximum transmi=
ssion unit
            from the DHCP server will be used on the current link.
            Defaults to false.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Anonymize=3D"><span class=
=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">Anonymize=3D</code></span><a class=3D"hea=
derlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.o=
rg/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#Anonymize=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><=
dd><p>Takes a boolean argument. When true, the options sent to the DHCP ser=
ver will
            follow the <a class=3D"ulink" href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/ht=
ml/rfc7844" target=3D"_top">RFC 7844</a>
            (Anonymity Profiles for DHCP Clients) to minimize disclosure of=
 identifying information.
            Defaults to false.</p><p>This option should only be set to true=
 when
            <code class=3D"varname">MACAddressPolicy=3D</code> is set to "<=
code class=3D"literal">random</code>"
            (see <a href=3D"http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man5/systemd.li=
nk.5.html"><span class=3D"citerefentry"><span class=3D"refentrytitle">syste=
md.link</span>(5)</span></a>).</p><p>Note that this configuration will over=
write others.
            In concrete, the following variables will be ignored:
            <code class=3D"varname">SendHostname=3D</code>, <code class=3D"=
varname">ClientIdentifier=3D</code>,
            <code class=3D"varname">UseRoutes=3D</code>, <code class=3D"var=
name">SendHostname=3D</code>,
            <code class=3D"varname">UseMTU=3D</code>, <code class=3D"varnam=
e">VendorClassIdentifier=3D</code>,
            <code class=3D"varname">UseTimezone=3D</code>.</p></dd><dt id=
=3D"SendHostname=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">SendHostn=
ame=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term=
" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.=
html#SendHostname=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>When true (the default), the ma=
chine's hostname will
            be sent to the DHCP server.</p></dd><dt id=3D"UseHostname=3D"><=
span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">UseHostname=3D</code></span><a =
class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.f=
reedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#UseHostname=3D">=
=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>When true (the default), the hostname received from
            the DHCP server will be set as the transient hostname of the sy=
stem
            </p></dd><dt id=3D"Hostname=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code clas=
s=3D"varname">Hostname=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Per=
malink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/m=
an/systemd.network.html#Hostname=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Use this value f=
or the hostname which is sent to the
          DHCP server, instead of machine's hostname.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Use=
Domains=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">UseDomains=3D</cod=
e></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"h=
ttps://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#UseDom=
ains=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Takes a boolean argument, or the special val=
ue "<code class=3D"literal">route</code>". When true, the domain name
            received from the DHCP server will be used as DNS search domain=
 over this link, similar to the effect of
            the <code class=3D"option">Domains=3D</code> setting. If set to=
 "<code class=3D"literal">route</code>", the domain name received from
            the DHCP server will be used for routing DNS queries only, but =
not for searching, similar to the effect of
            the <code class=3D"option">Domains=3D</code> setting when the a=
rgument is prefixed with "<code class=3D"literal">~</code>". Defaults to
            false.</p><p>It is recommended to enable this option only on tr=
usted networks, as setting this affects resolution
            of all host names, in particular of single-label names. It is g=
enerally safer to use the supplied domain
            only as routing domain, rather than as search domain, in order =
to not have it affect local resolution of
            single-label names.</p><p>When set to true, this setting corres=
ponds to the <code class=3D"option">domain</code> option in <a href=3D"http=
://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man5/resolv.conf.5.html"><span class=3D"citeref=
entry"><span class=3D"refentrytitle">resolv.conf</span>(5)</span></a>.</p><=
/dd><dt id=3D"UseRoutes=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">Us=
eRoutes=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this =
term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.netw=
ork.html#UseRoutes=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>When true (the default), the s=
tatic routes will be requested from the DHCP server and added to the
              routing table with a metric of 1024, and a scope of "global",=
 "link" or "host", depending on the route's
              destination and gateway. If the destination is on the local h=
ost, e.g., 127.x.x.x, or the same as the
              link's own address, the scope will be set to "host". Otherwis=
e if the gateway is null (a direct route), a
              "link" scope will be used. For anything else, scope defaults =
to "global".</p></dd><dt id=3D"UseTimezone=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code c=
lass=3D"varname">UseTimezone=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=
=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/sy=
stemd/man/systemd.network.html#UseTimezone=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>When t=
rue, the timezone received from the
          DHCP server will be set as timezone of the local
          system. Defaults to "<code class=3D"literal">no</code>".</p></dd>=
<dt id=3D"CriticalConnection=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varnam=
e">CriticalConnection=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Perm=
alink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/ma=
n/systemd.network.html#CriticalConnection=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>When tr=
ue, the connection will never be torn down
            even if the DHCP lease expires. This is contrary to the
            DHCP specification, but may be the best choice if, say,
            the root filesystem relies on this connection. Defaults to
            false.</p></dd><dt id=3D"ClientIdentifier=3D"><span class=3D"te=
rm"><code class=3D"varname">ClientIdentifier=3D</code></span><a class=3D"he=
aderlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.=
org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#ClientIdentifier=3D">=C2=B6</=
a></dt><dd><p>The DHCPv4 client identifier to use. Takes one of "<code clas=
s=3D"literal">mac</code>", "<code class=3D"literal">duid</code>" or "<code =
class=3D"literal">duid-only</code>".
            If set to "<code class=3D"literal">mac</code>", the MAC address=
 of the link is used.
            If set to "<code class=3D"literal">duid</code>", an RFC4361-com=
pliant Client ID, which is the combination of IAID and DUID (see below), is=
 used.
            If set to "<code class=3D"literal">duid-only</code>", only DUID=
 is used, this may not be RFC compliant, but some setups may require to use=
 this.
            Defaults to "<code class=3D"literal">duid</code>".</p></dd><dt =
id=3D"VendorClassIdentifier=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname=
">VendorClassIdentifier=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Pe=
rmalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/=
man/systemd.network.html#VendorClassIdentifier=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Th=
e vendor class identifier used to identify vendor
            type and configuration.</p></dd><dt id=3D"DUIDType=3D"><span cl=
ass=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">DUIDType=3D</code></span><a class=3D"h=
eaderlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop=
.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#DUIDType=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt>=
<dd><p>Override the global <code class=3D"varname">DUIDType</code> setting =
for this network. See
            <a href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/net=
workd.conf.html#"><span class=3D"citerefentry"><span class=3D"refentrytitle=
">networkd.conf</span>(5)</span></a>
            for a description of possible values.</p></dd><dt id=3D"DUIDRaw=
Data=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">DUIDRawData=3D</code>=
</span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#DUIDRawD=
ata=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Override the global <code class=3D"varname">D=
UIDRawData</code> setting for this network. See
            <a href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/net=
workd.conf.html#"><span class=3D"citerefentry"><span class=3D"refentrytitle=
">networkd.conf</span>(5)</span></a>
            for a description of possible values.</p></dd><dt id=3D"IAID=3D=
"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">IAID=3D</code></span><a clas=
s=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freed=
esktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#IAID=3D">=C2=B6</a></d=
t><dd><p>The DHCP Identity Association Identifier (IAID) for the interface,=
 a 32-bit unsigned integer.</p></dd><dt id=3D"RequestBroadcast=3D"><span cl=
ass=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">RequestBroadcast=3D</code></span><a cl=
ass=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.fre=
edesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#RequestBroadcast=3D"=
>=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Request the server to use broadcast messages before
            the IP address has been configured. This is necessary for
            devices that cannot receive RAW packets, or that cannot
            receive packets at all before an IP address has been
            configured. On the other hand, this must not be enabled on
            networks where broadcasts are filtered out.</p></dd><dt id=3D"R=
outeMetric=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">RouteMetric=3D<=
