=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#R=
outeMetric=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Set the routing metric for routes spec=
ified by the
            DHCP server.</p></dd><dt id=3D"RouteTable=3Dnum"><span class=3D=
"term"><code class=3D"varname">RouteTable=3D<em class=3D"replaceable"><code=
>num</code></em></code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to=
 this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/system=
d.network.html#RouteTable=3Dnum">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The table identifier=
 for DHCP routes (a number between 1 and 4294967295, or 0 to unset).
            The table can be retrieved using <span class=3D"command"><stron=
g>ip route show table <em class=3D"replaceable"><code>num</code></em></stro=
ng></span>.
            </p><p>When used in combination with <code class=3D"varname">VR=
F=3D</code> the
            VRF's routing table is used unless this parameter is specified.
            </p></dd><dt id=3D"ListenPort=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code cl=
ass=3D"varname">ListenPort=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D=
"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/syste=
md/man/systemd.network.html#ListenPort=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Allow sett=
ing custom port for the DHCP client to listen on.</p></dd><dt id=3D"RapidCo=
mmit=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">RapidCommit=3D</code>=
</span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#RapidCom=
mit=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>A boolean. The DHCPv6 client can obtain confi=
guration parameters from a DHCPv6 server through
            a rapid two-message exchange (solicit and reply). When the rapi=
d commit option is enabled by both
            the DHCPv6 client and the DHCPv6 server, the two-message exchan=
ge is used, rather than the default
            four-method exchange (solicit, advertise, request, and reply). =
The two-message exchange provides
            faster client configuration and is beneficial in environments i=
n which networks are under a heavy load.
            See <a class=3D"ulink" href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3=
315#section-17.2.1" target=3D"_top">RFC 3315</a> for details.
            Defaults to true.</p></dd></dl></div></div><div class=3D"refsec=
