 class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">Managed=3D</code>, </span><span cla=
ss=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">OtherInformation=3D</code></span><a cla=
ss=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.free=
desktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#Managed=3D">=C2=B6</a=
></dt><dd><p>Controls whether a DHCPv6 server is used to acquire IPv6
        addresses on the network link when <code class=3D"varname">Managed=
=3D</code> boolean
        is set to "<code class=3D"literal">true</code>" or if only addition=
al network
        information can be obtained via DHCPv6 for the network link when
        <code class=3D"varname">OtherInformation=3D</code> boolean is set t=
o
        "<code class=3D"literal">true</code>". Both settings default to
        "<code class=3D"literal">false</code>", which means that a DHCPv6 s=
erver is not being
        used.</p></dd><dt id=3D"RouterLifetimeSec=3D"><span class=3D"term">=
<code class=3D"varname">RouterLifetimeSec=3D</code></span><a class=3D"heade=
rlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org=
/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#RouterLifetimeSec=3D">=C2=B6</a>=
</dt><dd><p>Configures the IPv6 router lifetime in seconds. If set,
        this host also announces itself in Router Advertisements as an IPv6
        router for the network link. Defaults to unset, which means the hos=
t is
        not acting as a router.</p></dd><dt id=3D"RouterPreference=3D"><spa=
n class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">RouterPreference=3D</code></span><=
a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www=
.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#RouterPreference=
=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Configures IPv6 router preference if
        <code class=3D"varname">RouterLifetimeSec=3D</code> is non-zero. Va=
lid values are
        "<code class=3D"literal">high</code>", "<code class=3D"literal">med=
ium</code>" and
        "<code class=3D"literal">low</code>", with "<code class=3D"literal"=
>normal</code>" and
        "<code class=3D"literal">default</code>" added as synonyms for
        "<code class=3D"literal">medium</code>" just to make configuration =
easier. See
        <a class=3D"ulink" href=3D"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4191" tar=
get=3D"_top">RFC 4191</a>
        for details. Defaults to "<code class=3D"literal">medium</code>".</=
p></dd><dt id=3D"EmitDNS=3D1"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">=
EmitDNS=3D</code>, </span><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">DNS=
=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" h=
ref=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.htm=
l#EmitDNS=3D1">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p><code class=3D"varname">DNS=3D</code> =
specifies a list of recursive
        DNS server IPv6 addresses that distributed via Router Advertisement
        messages when <code class=3D"varname">EmitDNS=3D</code> is true. If=
 <code class=3D"varname">DNS=3D
        </code> is empty, DNS servers are read from the
        "<code class=3D"literal">[Network]</code>" section. If the
        "<code class=3D"literal">[Network]</code>" section does not contain=
 any DNS servers
        either, DNS servers from the uplink with the highest priority defau=
lt
        route are used. When <code class=3D"varname">EmitDNS=3D</code> is f=
alse, no DNS server
        information is sent in Router Advertisement messages.
        <code class=3D"varname">EmitDNS=3D</code> defaults to true.
        </p></dd><dt id=3D"EmitDomains=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=
=3D"varname">EmitDomains=3D</code>, </span><span class=3D"term"><code class=
=3D"varname">Domains=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Perma=
link to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man=
/systemd.network.html#EmitDomains=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>A list of DNS s=
earch domains distributed via Router
        Advertisement messages when <code class=3D"varname">EmitDomains=3D<=
/code> is true. If
        <code class=3D"varname">Domains=3D</code> is empty, DNS search doma=
ins are read from the
        "<code class=3D"literal">[Network]</code>" section. If the "<code c=
lass=3D"literal">[Network]</code>"
        section does not contain any DNS search domains either, DNS search
        domains from the uplink with the highest priority default route are
        used. When <code class=3D"varname">EmitDomains=3D</code> is false, =
no DNS search domain
        information is sent in Router Advertisement messages.
        <code class=3D"varname">EmitDomains=3D</code> defaults to true.
        </p></dd><dt id=3D"DNSLifetimeSec=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code cl=
ass=3D"varname">DNSLifetimeSec=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" titl=
e=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/s=
ystemd/man/systemd.network.html#DNSLifetimeSec=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Li=
fetime in seconds for the DNS server addresses listed
        in <code class=3D"varname">DNS=3D</code> and search domains listed =
in
        <code class=3D"varname">Domains=3D</code>.</p></dd></dl></div></div=
