        "<code class=3D"literal">/</code>" character. Use multiple
        "<code class=3D"literal">[IPv6Prefix]</code>" sections to configure=
 multiple IPv6
        prefixes since prefix lifetimes, address autoconfiguration and onli=
nk
        status may differ from one prefix to another.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Pre=
ferredLifetimeSec=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">Preferre=
dLifetimeSec=3D</code>, </span><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname"=
>ValidLifetimeSec=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalin=
k to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/sy=
stemd.network.html#PreferredLifetimeSec=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Preferred=
 and valid lifetimes for the prefix measured in
        seconds. <code class=3D"varname">PreferredLifetimeSec=3D</code> def=
aults to 604800
        seconds (one week) and <code class=3D"varname">ValidLifetimeSec=3D<=
/code> defaults
        to 2592000 seconds (30 days).</p></dd></dl></div></div><div class=
=3D"refsect1"><a name=3D"id-1.18"></a><h2 id=3D"[Bridge] Section Options">[=
