><code class=3D"varname">Cost=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=
=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/sy=
stemd/man/systemd.network.html#Cost=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Sets the "cos=
t" of sending packets of this interface.
            Each port in a bridge may have a different speed and the cost
            is used to decide which link to use. Faster interfaces
            should have lower costs. It is an integer value between 1 and
            65535.</p></dd><dt id=3D"Priority=3D1"><span class=3D"term"><co=
de class=3D"varname">Priority=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=
=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/sy=
stemd/man/systemd.network.html#Priority=3D1">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>Sets the=
 "priority" of sending packets on this interface.
            Each port in a bridge may have a different priority which is us=
ed
            to decide which link to use. Lower value means higher priority.
            It is an integer value between 0 to 63. Networkd does not set a=
ny
            default, meaning the kernel default value of 32 is used.</p></d=
d></dl></div></div><div class=3D"refsect1"><a name=3D"id-1.19"></a><h2 id=
=3D"[BridgeFDB] Section Options">[BridgeFDB] Section Options<a class=3D"hea=
derlink" title=3D"Permalink to this headline" href=3D"https://www.freedeskt=
op.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#%5BBridgeFDB%5D%20Section%=
20Options">=C2=B6</a></h2><p>The "<code class=3D"literal">[BridgeFDB]</code=
>" section manages the
      forwarding database table of a port and accepts the following
      keys. Specify several "<code class=3D"literal">[BridgeFDB]</code>" se=
ctions to
      configure several static MAC table entries.</p><div class=3D"variable=
list"><dl class=3D"variablelist"><dt id=3D"MACAddress=3D2"><span class=3D"t=
erm"><code class=3D"varname">MACAddress=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerl=
ink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/s=
oftware/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#MACAddress=3D2">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd=
><p>As in the "<code class=3D"literal">[Network]</code>" section. This
            key is mandatory.</p></dd><dt id=3D"VLANId=3D"><span class=3D"t=
erm"><code class=3D"varname">VLANId=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink"=
 title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/softw=
are/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#VLANId=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The V=
LAN ID for the new static MAC table entry. If
            omitted, no VLAN ID information is appended to the new static M=
AC
            table entry.</p></dd></dl></div></div><div class=3D"refsect1"><=
a name=3D"id-1.20"></a><h2 id=3D"[BridgeVLAN] Section Options">[BridgeVLAN]=
 Section Options<a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this headline=
" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.=
html#%5BBridgeVLAN%5D%20Section%20Options">=C2=B6</a></h2><p>The "<code cla=
ss=3D"literal">[BridgeVLAN]</code>" section manages the VLAN ID configurati=
on of a bridge port and accepts
      the following keys. Specify several "<code class=3D"literal">[BridgeV=
LAN]</code>" sections to configure several VLAN entries.
      The <code class=3D"varname">VLANFiltering=3D</code> option has to be =
enabled, see "<code class=3D"literal">[Bridge]</code>" section in
      <a href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.n=
etdev.html#"><span class=3D"citerefentry"><span class=3D"refentrytitle">sys=
temd.netdev</span>(5)</span></a>.</p><div class=3D"variablelist"><dl class=
=3D"variablelist"><dt id=3D"VLAN=3D1"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D"v=
arname">VLAN=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to =
this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd=
.network.html#VLAN=3D1">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The VLAN ID allowed on the po=
rt. This can be either a single ID or a range M-N. VLAN IDs are valid
            from 1 to 4094.</p></dd><dt id=3D"EgressUntagged=3D"><span clas=
s=3D"term"><code class=3D"varname">EgressUntagged=3D</code></span><a class=
=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink to this term" href=3D"https://www.freede=
sktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#EgressUntagged=3D">=C2=
=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The VLAN ID specified here will be used to untag frames =
on egress. Configuring
            <code class=3D"varname">EgressUntagged=3D</code> implicates the=
 use of <code class=3D"varname">VLAN=3D</code> above and will enable the
            VLAN ID for ingress as well. This can be either a single ID or =
a range M-N.</p></dd><dt id=3D"PVID=3D"><span class=3D"term"><code class=3D=
"varname">PVID=3D</code></span><a class=3D"headerlink" title=3D"Permalink t=
o this term" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/syste=
md.network.html#PVID=3D">=C2=B6</a></dt><dd><p>The Port VLAN ID specified h=
ere is assigned to all untagged frames at ingress.
            <code class=3D"varname">PVID=3D</code> can be used only once. C=
onfiguring <code class=3D"varname">PVID=3D</code> implicates the use of
            <code class=3D"varname">VLAN=3D</code> above and will enable th=
e VLAN ID for ingress as well.</p></dd></dl></div></div><div class=3D"refse=
ct1"><a name=3D"id-1.21"></a><h2 id=3D"Examples">Examples<a class=3D"header=
link" title=3D"Permalink to this headline" href=3D"https://www.freedesktop.=
org/software/systemd/man/systemd.network.html#Examples">=C2=B6</a></h2><div=
 class=3D"example"><a name=3D"id-1.21.2"></a><p class=3D"title"><b>Example&=
nbsp;1.&nbsp;Static network configuration</b></p><div class=3D"example-cont=
ents"><pre class=3D"programlisting"># /etc/systemd/network/50-static.networ=
k
[Match]
Name=3Denp2s0

[Network]
Address=3D192.168.0.15/24
Gateway=3D192.168.0.1</pre><p>This brings interface "<code class=3D"literal=
">enp2s0</code>" up with a static address. The
      specified gateway will be used for a default route.</p></div></div><b=
r class=3D"example-break"><div class=3D"example"><a name=3D"id-1.21.3"></a>=
<p class=3D"title"><b>Example&nbsp;2.&nbsp;DHCP on ethernet links</b></p><d=
iv class=3D"example-contents"><pre class=3D"programlisting"># /etc/systemd/=
network/80-dhcp.network
[Match]
Name=3Den*

[Network]
DHCP=3Dyes</pre><p>This will enable DHCPv4 and DHCPv6 on all interfaces wit=
h names starting with
      "<code class=3D"literal">en</code>" (i.e. ethernet interfaces).</p></=
div></div><br class=3D"example-break"><div class=3D"example"><a name=3D"id-=
1.21.4"></a><p class=3D"title"><b>Example&nbsp;3.&nbsp;A bridge with two en=
slaved links</b></p><div class=3D"example-contents"><pre class=3D"programli=
sting"># /etc/systemd/network/25-bridge-static.network
[Match]
Name=3Dbridge0

[Network]
Address=3D192.168.0.15/24
Gateway=3D192.168.0.1
DNS=3D192.168.0.1</pre><pre class=3D"programlisting"># /etc/systemd/network=
/25-bridge-slave-interface-1.network
[Match]
Name=3Denp2s0

[Network]
Bridge=3Dbridge0</pre><pre class=3D"programlisting"># /etc/systemd/network/=
25-bridge-slave-interface-2.network
[Match]
Name=3Dwlp3s0

[Network]
Bridge=3Dbridge0</pre><p>This creates a bridge and attaches devices "<code =
class=3D"literal">enp2s0</code>" and
      "<code class=3D"literal">wlp3s0</code>" to it. The bridge will have t=
he specified static address
      and network assigned, and a default route via the specified gateway w=
ill be
      added. The specified DNS server will be added to the global list of D=
NS resolvers.
      </p></div></div><br class=3D"example-break"><div class=3D"example"><a=
 name=3D"id-1.21.5"></a><p class=3D"title"><b>Example&nbsp;4.&nbsp;</b></p>=
<div class=3D"example-contents"><pre class=3D"programlisting"># /etc/system=
d/network/20-bridge-slave-interface-vlan.network
[Match]
Name=3Denp2s0

[Network]
Bridge=3Dbridge0

[BridgeVLAN]
VLAN=3D1-32
PVID=3D42
EgressUntagged=3D42

[BridgeVLAN]
VLAN=3D100-200

[BridgeVLAN]
EgressUntagged=3D300-400</pre><p>This overrides the configuration specified=
 in the previous example for the
    interface "<code class=3D"literal">enp2s0</code>", and enables VLAN on =
that bridge port. VLAN IDs
    1-32, 42, 100-400 will be allowed. Packets tagged with VLAN IDs 42, 300=
-400 will be
    untagged when they leave on this interface. Untagged packets which arri=
ve on this
    interface will be assigned VLAN ID 42.</p></div></div><br class=3D"exam=
ple-break"><div class=3D"example"><a name=3D"id-1.21.6"></a><p class=3D"tit=
le"><b>Example&nbsp;5.&nbsp;Various tunnels</b></p><div class=3D"example-co=
ntents"><pre class=3D"programlisting">/etc/systemd/network/25-tunnels.netwo=
rk
[Match]
Name=3Dens1

[Network]
